External knowledge:
- Average rating is an indicator of the overall quality of a casino based on user reviews;
- Sign-up bonuses are incentives offered by casinos to attract new users;
- A higher number of ratings and reviews generally indicates more user engagement and trustworthiness of the casino.

sql:
SELECT title, bonus
FROM casinos
WHERE bonus = (SELECT MAX(bonus) FROM casinos);

SELECT title, rating
FROM casinos
ORDER BY rating DESC;

SELECT maximum_bonus_amount
FROM bonus_types
WHERE bonus_type_name = 'Sign-up Bonus';

external_knowledge:
This question assumes that the ratings are based on user reviews or some other form of evaluation; 
The average rating is a measure of the overall quality or reputation of each casino; 
Casinos that offer bonuses may be considered more attractive to potential customers.

sql:
SELECT title, bonus
FROM casinos
WHERE casino_id = 1;

SELECT DISTINCT email
FROM users
WHERE user_id IN (
  SELECT user_id
  FROM ratings
);

SELECT bonus_type_name
FROM bonus_types
WHERE bonus_type_id = 0;

SELECT casino_id, title, AVG(rating) AS average_rating
FROM casinos
GROUP BY casino_id, title;

external_knowledge:
casinos established after the year 2000 refers to casinos with an establishment year greater than or equal to 2000; 
more than 200 games refers to casinos with a number of games greater than 200; 
average user age is calculated by subtracting the user's birth year from the current year; 
users whose first name starts with 'A' refers to users whose first name begins with the letter 'A'; 
users whose first name does not start with 'A' refers to users whose first name begins with any letter other than 'A'.

"most popular" refers to casinos with more than five unique users who have reviewed them and at least one review; 
"generous" refers to casinos offering a high total bonus amount; 
"overall satisfaction" refers to the average rating of a casino; 
"many customers" refers to casinos with more than five unique users who have reviewed them.
